The article announces an upcoming event at the White House called "In Performance at the White House: Memphis Soul." The event will celebrate Memphis Soul music and will feature performances by various artists, including Alabama Shakes, Al Green, Cyndi Lauper, and Justin Timberlake. The President's remarks will be pooled press and the event will be streamed live on the White House website. The event will be broadcast on PBS stations on April 16 and will also be broadcast later on the American Forces Network. In addition, the First Lady will host a daytime event for students, where they will learn about the history of Memphis Soul and have the opportunity to interact with the performers. The student workshop will also be streamed live on the White House website. This will be the tenth "In Performance at the White House" program hosted by President and Mrs. Obama.